Rock, Paper, Scissors Game

Overview :
Welcome to the Rock, Paper, Scissors game! This simple Python program allows you to play the classic game against the computer.

How to Play:
Clone this repository to your local machine.
Open a terminal and navigate to the project directory.
Run the rps.py file using Python: rps.py
Follow the on-screen instructions to make your move (rock, paper, or scissors).
See if you can outsmart the computer and win the game!

Features:
User-friendly interface for an easy and enjoyable gaming experience.
Randomized computer moves to keep the game unpredictable.
Simple code structure, making it a great starting point for Python beginners.

Requirements:
Python 3.x

Usage: 
Feel free to use and modify the code for your learning and development purposes. If you come up with improvements, consider contributing to make this project even better!

